Here is a function that can be used to find the maximum element in the given array:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int findMaximum(int array[], int numElements) {
  int max = array[0];

  for (int i = 1; i < numElements; i++) {
    if (array[i] > max) {
      max = array[i];
    }
  }
  return max;
}

int main() {
  int array[] = {8, 3, 5, 9, 3, 1, 5};
  int numElements = sizeof(array)/sizeof(array[0]);
  int max = findMaximum(array, numElements );
  printf("The maximum element in the given array is %d.", max);
  return 0;
}
```

This function takes two arguments: the array and the number of elements in it. It initializes the variable `max` with the value of the first element in the array. Then it loops through the rest of the elements in the array and compares each element with the current value of `max`. If an element is greater than the current `max`, it updates the value of `max` with that element. Finally, the function returns the maximum value found in the array.
